### Operating System

Linux

### What's the issue you encountered?

I have made a pattern for an [IFF](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interchange_File_Format) file I have, it uses a searcher pattern for finding the children of the AUDO chunk.

When I run my pattern on my 190 MB IFF file, it will consume all 16 GB memory I have free on my system, while still not completing pattern placement. If I limit searching chunks to slightly less than half of it, pattern placement completes with 4,8 GB of RAM usage.

I have read #1258 , and indeed I am using a 4 byte local variable (a string), but the while loop will only run ~~37~~ 58 times, so in my understanding this local variable should only take up 4\*58=232 bytes for the whole dataset (or 5\*58 if read_string also returns a zero byte at the end of the string).

If I stop evaluation when for all 10 expected searched items a green bar appears in the progress bar, roughly at 4 GB memory usage, all 10 expected records will be visible in the pattern data view in their complete form, and memory usage will fall back to ~300-400 MB of RAM.
If I dont stop evaluation, memory usage shortly falls back, but then continues to rise, then the green bars disappear one by one, and when I eventually have to stop it at 9 GB the memory usage will not fall back, and I will have the same results in the pattern data view.

This sounds like 2 issues to me:
- temporary memory leak while placing patterns
- permanent memory leak when continuing to read through the end of the file?

### How can the issue be reproduced?

The IFF file is too big for github, so I uploaded it here: https://big.grin.hu/ngzE2O/data.dat
It will stay available for an undetermined amount of time. If it disappears but you wanted to use it, please let me know in a comment and I will reupload.

Use this pattern with the IFF file:
```
import std.mem;
import std.io;

u32 counter = 0;

struct RIFFChunk {
    char id[4];
    u32 chunkSize;
    u8 data[chunkSize];
};

struct RIFFBlock {
    char signature[4];      // "RIFF"
    u32 totalSize;          // Size of everything after this field
    char format[4];         // "WAVE"

    RIFFChunk fmt_chunk;
    RIFFChunk list_chunk;
    RIFFChunk data_chunk;
};

struct AudoChunkChildSearcher {
    str test_str = std::mem::read_string($, 4);

    counter += 1;
    std::print(counter);

    if (test_str == "RIFF") {
        RIFFBlock riff @ $;
        $ += sizeof(riff);
    } else if (!std::mem::eof()) {
        $ += 1; continue;
    } else {
        break;
    }
};

struct AudoChunk {
    char type[4];      // "AUDO"
    s32 chunk_size;

    // this needs to be stopped manually:
    AudoChunkChildSearcher inner_chunks[while(!std::mem::eof())];
    // this runs to completion, but is still leaking memory
    //AudoChunkChildSearcher inner_chunks[while($ < 0x04000000)];
};

struct FormChunk {
    char type_id[4];      // "FORM"
    s32 chunk_size;

    AudoChunk audo_chunk;
};

FormChunk form_chunk @ 0x0;
```

